<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2012/05/11/video-more-practical-tips-and-tricks-with-spring-integration">Video: More Practical Tips and Tricks with Spring Integration</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon news-and-events"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/news">News and Events</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="null?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<span class="author">Adam Fitzgerald</span>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2012-05-11 17:17:00.0">May 11, 2012</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="559" href="/blog/2012/05/11/video-more-practical-tips-and-tricks-with-spring-integration#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>This video provides a follow-up session to <a href="http://blog.springsource.org/author/ozhurakousky/">Oleg Zhurakousky</a>'s successful <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RY6dNUL8k6o">Spring Integration Tips and Tricks</a> webinar exploring deeper and more complex patterns for integration. The questions for this session came out of the actual customer engagements as well as the questions that are most frequently asked on the Spring Integration forums. In this edition of "Practical Tips-and-Tricks" Oleg covers the advanced topics of enterprise integration such as advanced aggregation and resequencing, asynchronous message flows, message ID customizations, content enrichment and advanced message routing and more. This video is based on a refined version of <a href="http://www.infoq.com/presentations/Spring-Integration-Practical-Tips-and-Tricks">Oleg's very successful talk delivered at SpringOne 2GX 2011</a>.</p>
</div>
</section>
